00:22:05.020 --> 00:22:06.061 align:middle line:90%
what would you tell them?

00:22:06.061 --> 00:22:07.920 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, we are
afraid of the unknown.

00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:08.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:22:08.720 --> 00:22:10.260 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, we
can say knowledge

00:22:10.260 --> 00:22:12.170 align:middle line:90%
is afraid of the unknown.

00:22:12.170 --> 00:22:14.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:22:14.380 --> 00:22:17.686 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And knowledge is
just a reflection of life.

00:22:17.686 --> 00:22:19.310 align:middle line:84%
The whole story's a
reflection of life.

00:22:19.310 --> 00:22:22.570 align:middle line:90%
Is that even real?

00:22:22.570 --> 00:22:28.270 align:middle line:84%
And knowledge believes that
it is the physical body.

00:22:28.270 --> 00:22:29.780 align:middle line:90%
Because we see it all the time.

00:22:29.780 --> 00:22:30.720 align:middle line:90%
We feel it.

00:22:30.720 --> 00:22:34.280 align:middle line:84%
We create emotions,
et cetera, et cetera.

00:22:34.280 --> 00:22:36.310 align:middle line:90%
But we are not physical body.

00:22:36.310 --> 00:22:40.420 align:middle line:84%
Then the way we see that
is completely different.

00:22:40.420 --> 00:22:42.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: When you were
in the coma, what

00:22:42.690 --> 00:22:47.530 align:middle line:84%
was your experience of
what would be called death?

00:22:47.530 --> 00:22:48.960 align:middle line:90%
What is your experience?

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:52.930 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, I was so excited
when I had the heart attack.

00:22:52.930 --> 00:22:55.975 align:middle line:84%
For in the morning, I
woke up with a strong pain

00:22:55.975 --> 00:22:57.600 align:middle line:90%
in the chest.

00:22:57.600 --> 00:22:59.150 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I'm
a medical doctor.

00:22:59.150 --> 00:23:00.910 align:middle line:90%
I know it's a heart attack.

00:23:00.910 --> 00:23:04.340 align:middle line:84%
And one of symptoms is
that you know you're dying.

00:23:04.340 --> 00:23:06.980 align:middle line:90%
It's the sensation of death.

00:23:06.980 --> 00:23:09.556 align:middle line:90%
My head is, this is it.

00:23:09.556 --> 00:23:12.100 align:middle line:84%
I had a strong pain,
but I was very excited.

00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:16.210 align:middle line:84%
OK, finally, I will
have the experience

00:23:16.210 --> 00:23:18.020 align:middle line:90%
how to leave my physical body.

00:23:18.020 --> 00:23:18.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:23:18.820 --> 00:23:20.970 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And because
of course, before I

00:23:20.970 --> 00:23:22.920 align:middle line:84%
knew I'm not a
physical body-- I had

00:23:22.920 --> 00:23:25.936 align:middle line:90%
many other experiences before.

00:23:25.936 --> 00:23:29.260 align:middle line:84%
I completely cannot separate
from my physical body.

00:23:29.260 --> 00:23:31.570 align:middle line:84%
And I said, my physical
body is my home,

00:23:31.570 --> 00:23:36.180 align:middle line:84%
my sanctuary where I live,
and I honor and I respect.

00:23:36.180 --> 00:23:39.970 align:middle line:84%
But to live in my physical body,
it was the greatest experience,

00:23:39.970 --> 00:23:42.730 align:middle line:84%
and I want everybody
to see that experience,

00:23:42.730 --> 00:23:44.350 align:middle line:90%
to learn from that experience.

00:23:44.350 --> 00:23:48.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, just a little
before that I

00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:52.740 align:middle line:84%
go to coma, my middle
son don Jose Ruiz,

00:23:52.740 --> 00:23:57.090 align:middle line:90%
he came to see me from Malibu.

00:23:57.090 --> 00:23:59.730 align:middle line:90%
I was in San Diego.

00:23:59.730 --> 00:24:03.880 align:middle line:84%
And we just came back
from a journey to Tijuana

00:24:03.880 --> 00:24:06.940 align:middle line:84%
where I teach all
my apprentices.

00:24:06.940 --> 00:24:10.394 align:middle line:84%
And I was so happy
when he came to see me.

00:24:10.394 --> 00:24:14.580 align:middle line:84%
I really wanted-- but
then, I see his face.

00:24:14.580 --> 00:24:18.500 align:middle line:84%
I start talking, and
everything changed.

00:24:18.500 --> 00:24:20.010 align:middle line:90%
I see that he was grieving.

00:24:20.010 --> 00:24:21.450 align:middle line:90%
He was afraid.

00:24:21.450 --> 00:24:25.370 align:middle line:84%
He tells me, father,
please, don't die.

00:24:25.370 --> 00:24:27.380 align:middle line:90%
Don't leave me alone.

00:24:27.380 --> 00:24:29.855 align:middle line:90%
I'm not ready yet.

00:24:29.855 --> 00:24:33.515 align:middle line:84%
And then my smile
changed a little.

00:24:33.515 --> 00:24:35.180 align:middle line:90%
It was a little more severe.

00:24:35.180 --> 00:24:38.870 align:middle line:84%
I look into his
eyes and say, Jose,

00:24:38.870 --> 00:24:40.820 align:middle line:84%
is this the way that
you will celebrate

00:24:40.820 --> 00:24:42.285 align:middle line:90%
the death of your father?

00:24:42.285 --> 00:24:43.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS] Oh, god.

00:24:43.650 --> 00:24:46.600 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Get out of the room.

00:24:46.600 --> 00:24:48.820 align:middle line:90%
Fix yourself, and come back.

00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Because I have something
very important to tell you.

00:24:52.880 --> 00:24:55.590 align:middle line:90%
It was a big shock for him.

00:24:55.590 --> 00:24:58.710 align:middle line:90%
And anyway, he went out.

00:24:58.710 --> 00:25:04.120 align:middle line:84%
And all [INAUDIBLE] in
his mind right away.

00:25:04.120 --> 00:25:07.800 align:middle line:90%
It shift places.

00:25:07.800 --> 00:25:11.430 align:middle line:84%
In his imagination, he
was the one who was dying,

00:25:11.430 --> 00:25:15.000 align:middle line:84%
and I was the one who come a
say, please don't die, my son.

00:25:15.000 --> 00:25:16.477 align:middle line:84%
What am I going
to do without you?

00:25:16.477 --> 00:25:18.060 align:middle line:84%
And he go, in fact,
a littler further.

00:25:18.060 --> 00:25:20.420 align:middle line:90%
He already was dead.

00:25:20.420 --> 00:25:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And he saw me stop
writing, and start

00:25:23.710 --> 00:25:26.730 align:middle line:84%
traveling, and just
feeling sorry for myself,

00:25:26.730 --> 00:25:30.540 align:middle line:84%
and just crying and crying
because I don't see him

00:25:30.540 --> 00:25:32.220 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:25:32.220 --> 00:25:36.680 align:middle line:84%
Then in his imagination,
he has just a few moments

00:25:36.680 --> 00:25:44.020 align:middle line:84%
to talk to me before he leaves
forever, and say, father, stop.

00:25:44.020 --> 00:25:46.250 align:middle line:90%
I am completely happy.

00:25:46.250 --> 00:25:48.250 align:middle line:90%
I have no problems anymore.

00:25:48.250 --> 00:25:49.800 align:middle line:90%
Everything is great.

00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:50.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm calm.

00:25:50.690 --> 00:25:54.230 align:middle line:90%
But you are alive.

00:25:54.230 --> 00:25:55.580 align:middle line:90%
Live your life.

00:25:55.580 --> 00:26:00.430 align:middle line:84%
Keep doing what you know to
do, what gives you the passion.

00:26:00.430 --> 00:26:04.410 align:middle line:84%
After that, then he
came back into the room.

00:26:04.410 --> 00:26:05.360 align:middle line:90%
He grabbed my hand.

00:26:05.360 --> 00:26:07.750 align:middle line:84%
He kissed my hand, and
say, father, I am with you.

00:26:07.750 --> 00:26:08.930 align:middle line:90%
I understand now.

00:26:08.930 --> 00:26:09.825 align:middle line:90%
I've been so selfish.

00:26:09.825 --> 00:26:12.140 align:middle line:90%
Please forgive me.

00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:14.160 align:middle line:90%
I was thinking just about me.

00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:17.380 align:middle line:84%
And knowing that perhaps
it's the very last time

00:26:17.380 --> 00:26:20.000 align:middle line:84%
and you're so happy, I was
taking your happiness away

00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:24.021 align:middle line:84%
from you, just because
of my selfishness.

00:26:24.021 --> 00:26:26.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's a beautiful
story, and it's true.

00:26:26.020 --> 00:26:31.380 align:middle line:84%
We do give ourselves that
story of when someone dies.

00:26:31.380 --> 00:26:34.400 align:middle line:84%
But the one thing-- and
we just lost Wayne Dyer,

00:26:34.400 --> 00:26:37.820 align:middle line:84%
who's a strong mentor of mine
and an incredible friend.

00:26:37.820 --> 00:26:48.160 align:middle line:84%
And I still-- in my mind, my
story is, it was too soon.

00:26:48.160 --> 00:26:49.400 align:middle line:90%
It was too soon.

00:26:49.400 --> 00:26:53.220 align:middle line:84%
He really had so much more
life in him, I believed.

00:26:53.220 --> 00:26:55.180 align:middle line:90%
And I know that's my story.

00:26:55.180 --> 00:26:59.650 align:middle line:84%
But when we lose someone
too soon-- a child,

00:26:59.650 --> 00:27:03.400 align:middle line:84%
you know, who leaves
this world without fully

00:27:03.400 --> 00:27:09.910 align:middle line:84%
living a life-- that story
is so hard to let go of.

00:27:09.910 --> 00:27:12.580 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's a
very strong story.

00:27:12.580 --> 00:27:14.660 align:middle line:90%
How do you teach people to--

00:27:14.660 --> 00:27:16.860 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Well, it's very simple.

00:27:16.860 --> 00:27:19.540 align:middle line:84%
As you're saying, you're
talking about your story.

00:27:19.540 --> 00:27:20.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:27:20.420 --> 00:27:21.930 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: It's your story.

00:27:21.930 --> 00:27:24.070 align:middle line:84%
It's not fair that
he's just gone.

00:27:24.070 --> 00:27:26.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:27:26.540 --> 00:27:28.666 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: The Wayne Dyer
that you know is only

00:27:28.666 --> 00:27:29.790 align:middle line:90%
what you believe about him.

00:27:29.790 --> 00:27:32.090 align:middle line:90%
It's an extension of you.

00:27:32.090 --> 00:27:34.190 align:middle line:90%
It's not really him.

00:27:34.190 --> 00:27:40.102 align:middle line:84%
And yes, his physical body
died, but he is immortal.

00:27:40.102 --> 00:27:43.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: True, but what about a
child who didn't live a life?

00:27:43.540 --> 00:27:44.850 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Same thing.

00:27:44.850 --> 00:27:45.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:27:45.650 --> 00:27:49.790 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, of course, same
thing-- exactly the same thing.

00:27:49.790 --> 00:27:52.380 align:middle line:90%
Life is eternal.

00:27:52.380 --> 00:27:54.640 align:middle line:90%
He was giving life to the child.

00:27:54.640 --> 00:27:58.350 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, we can
live a few minutes.

00:27:58.350 --> 00:28:02.470 align:middle line:90%
We could live maybe a month.

00:28:02.470 --> 00:28:05.860 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we can
make it to birth.

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:08.860 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we can die
at 10 years, at 20.

00:28:08.860 --> 00:28:09.770 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

00:28:09.770 --> 00:28:12.020 align:middle line:90%
It's happening all the time.

00:28:12.020 --> 00:28:17.490 align:middle line:84%
It's life pushing matter,
giving life to matter.

00:28:17.490 --> 00:28:22.170 align:middle line:84%
And there's billions
everywhere, all the time.

00:28:22.170 --> 00:28:27.540 align:middle line:84%
Then you have to see which
point of view are we using.

00:28:27.540 --> 00:28:30.460 align:middle line:84%
When we use the point of
view of our own story,

00:28:30.460 --> 00:28:34.600 align:middle line:84%
we used to believe that
none of that is fair.

00:28:34.600 --> 00:28:35.400 align:middle line:90%
But it's not true.

00:28:35.400 --> 00:28:36.760 align:middle line:90%
It's just a story.

00:28:36.760 --> 00:28:38.590 align:middle line:90%
It's not even real.

00:28:38.590 --> 00:28:43.620 align:middle line:84%
And this is what you believe
and not necessarily is true.

00:28:43.620 --> 00:28:49.150 align:middle line:84%
It's some of the superstitions
that we have because truly,

00:28:49.150 --> 00:28:53.220 align:middle line:84%
you never knew the
real Wayne Dyer.

00:28:53.220 --> 00:28:55.760 align:middle line:84%
You only know what
you believe about him,

00:28:55.760 --> 00:28:57.520 align:middle line:90%
what he meant to do you.

00:28:57.520 --> 00:28:58.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:00.833 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: You see in your story,
it's everything about me.

00:29:00.833 --> 00:29:02.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:03.650 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:29:03.650 --> 00:29:05.510 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: It's is all about me.

00:29:05.510 --> 00:29:08.530 align:middle line:90%
And that's what my son Jose saw.

00:29:08.530 --> 00:29:11.020 align:middle line:90%
Oh god, it was my selfishness.

00:29:11.020 --> 00:29:12.957 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Wow, you could
look at that any way,

00:29:12.957 --> 00:29:14.040 align:middle line:90%
even the death of a child.

00:29:14.040 --> 00:29:17.070 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then, for me,
it's a celebration.

00:29:17.070 --> 00:29:20.140 align:middle line:84%
He don't have to deal
with that any longer.

00:29:20.140 --> 00:29:24.240 align:middle line:84%
He already lived his legacy--
wonderful books, videos,

00:29:24.240 --> 00:29:25.040 align:middle line:90%
everything.

00:29:25.040 --> 00:29:26.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Teachings, yes.

00:29:26.290 --> 00:29:29.430 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And that helped
to change humanity.

00:29:29.430 --> 00:29:33.375 align:middle line:84%
Then in the time that he
was in a physical body,

00:29:33.375 --> 00:29:34.175 align:middle line:90%
he was wonderful.

00:29:34.175 --> 00:29:36.330 align:middle line:90%
He was great.

00:29:36.330 --> 00:29:40.500 align:middle line:84%
But only he knew exactly
what happened in his story.

00:29:40.500 --> 00:29:43.200 align:middle line:90%
Nobody else does.

00:29:43.200 --> 00:29:47.850 align:middle line:84%
But it's also life working
in a physical body.

00:29:47.850 --> 00:29:51.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And I do-- I
love what you said about

00:29:51.250 --> 00:29:57.090 align:middle line:84%
that life is truly immortal,
that he is truly immortal.

00:29:57.090 --> 00:29:57.890 align:middle line:90%
And a--

00:29:57.890 --> 00:29:59.860 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then he didn't
die, but his body did.

00:29:59.860 --> 00:30:01.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And a child
wouldn't either.

00:30:01.920 --> 00:30:04.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this-- it would
unlock so much pain

00:30:04.610 --> 00:30:06.402 align:middle line:84%
for parents or people
who've lost children.

00:30:06.402 --> 00:30:07.568 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: In their story, yes.

00:30:07.568 --> 00:30:09.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In their story,
is to let go of that story

00:30:09.800 --> 00:30:14.280 align:middle line:84%
and to believe and to really
know that life is eternal, yes.

00:30:14.280 --> 00:30:17.630 align:middle line:10%
>>RUIZ: Then that
really didn't exist.

00:30:17.630 --> 00:30:20.210 align:middle line:10%
It's just matter.

00:30:20.210 --> 00:30:21.815 align:middle line:10%
It's just concepts in the mind.

00:30:21.815 --> 00:30:24.410 align:middle line:10%


00:30:24.410 --> 00:30:25.470 align:middle line:10%
Life is eternal.

00:30:25.470 --> 00:30:28.640 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yes, and that
death is a story.

00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:29.560 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Yes

00:30:29.560 --> 00:30:31.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's beautiful.

00:30:31.210 --> 00:30:32.170 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:30:32.170 --> 00:30:33.970 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Oh, and
you're very welcome.

00:30:33.970 --> 00:30:37.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, you're such
an amazing teacher,

00:30:37.300 --> 00:30:40.500 align:middle line:84%
and I'm so grateful
to have you here.

00:30:40.500 --> 00:30:43.760 align:middle line:84%
And your story is
truly immortal.

00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:44.870 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Our story,

00:30:44.870 --> 00:30:46.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Our story, yes.

00:30:46.350 --> 00:30:48.340 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Everybody's story.

00:30:48.340 --> 00:30:49.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thank you so much.

